CSSPrimer takes in a markup file and generates a css file of all the extracted ids and classes.

This is a repo for using css_primer as a gem, redcar plugin or just the terminal.

== Terminal usage
  As a ruby gem:
    css_primer -h
  
  Or you can just:
    cd lib
    ruby terminal.rb -h

== Using Examples
  cd lib/
    ruby main.rb --in ../examples/test.html
    ruby main.rb --in ../examples/test.xml --out some_styles.css

== Dependencies
  Core Lib
  - ostruct
  - optparse
  - fileutils

== Tests
  You need rspec http://rspec.info/

  cd tests/
  rspec css_primer.rspec

